"title": "4918: dawn",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4918",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The time marked by the rising of the sun. It signals the end of night and relief from its attendant concerns, and the approach of daylight with the opportunity for renewed daily activity. The light of dawn following darkness is a symbol of hope and vindication, fulfilled especially in the coming of the Messiah through whom God's new age dawns.</p>\n<h2>Dawn as the end of the night</h2>\n<h3>It ends the darkness of the night</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:8\">AMO 5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:4\">2SA 23:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:18\">JOB 41:18</a></p>\n<h3>It signals the end of nightly activity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:22-Gen32:26\">GEN 32:22–32:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:25-Judg19:26\">JDG 19:25–19:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:36\">1SA 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:36\">1SA 25:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:32\">2SA 2:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam17:22\">2SA 17:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:16-Song2:17\">SNG 2:16–2:17</a></p>\n<h3>Waiting for the dawn to bring relief</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:6\">PSA 130:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:3-Job7:4\">JOB 7:3–7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:5\">PSA 46:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:12\">ISA 21:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:13\">ISA 38:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:29\">ACT 27:29</a></p>\n<h2>Dawn as the beginning of a new day</h2>\n<h3>It provides the earliest opportunity of the day</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:19\">DAN 6:19</a></strong> <em>First light provides the earliest opportunity for action and implies urgency.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:15\">GEN 19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:15\">JOS 6:15</a> <em>Dawn was a common time for military campaigns to begin</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:33\">JDG 9:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:2\">JDG 16:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:11\">1SA 19:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:1\">MAT 28:1</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:2\">MRK 16:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:1\">LUK 24:1</a> <em>Women visit Jesus Christ's tomb at dawn</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:35\">MRK 1:35</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:42\">LUK 4:42</a> <em>Jesus Christ prays at dawn</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:66\">LUK 22:66</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:2\">JHN 8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:33\">ACT 27:33</a></p>\n<h3>Important activity begins at dawn</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:21\">NEH 4:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:3\">NEH 8:3</a></p>\n<h2>Dawn as a symbol of blessings to come</h2>\n<h3>The Messiah brings a new dawn</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:2\">ISA 9:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:16\">REV 22:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:17\">NUM 24:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:16\">MAT 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:78-Luke1:79\">LUK 1:78–1:79</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:4-John1:5\">JHN 1:4–1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:12\">JHN 8:12</a></p>\n<h3>A symbol of hope and vindication</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:6\">PSA 37:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps112:4\">PSA 112:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:31\">JDG 5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:8\">PSA 57:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps108:2\">PSA 108:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:18\">PRO 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:8\">ISA 58:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:1-Isa60:3\">ISA 60:1–60:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:1\">ISA 62:1</a></p>\n<h3>A symbol of God's coming in glory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:3-Hab3:4\">HAB 3:3–3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:2\">MAL 4:2</a></p>\n<h3>A symbol of renewal</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:3\">PSA 110:3</a></p>\n<h2>Dawn as a symbol of God's revelation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:8\">1JN 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:20\">ISA 8:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:19\">2PE 1:19</a></p>\n<h2>Dawn as a time of reckoning</h2>\n<h3>Darkness at dawn as a picture of judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:10-Isa13:11\">ISA 13:10–13:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:9\">JOB 3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:13\">AMO 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>The light of dawn exposes the wicked</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:12-Job38:13\">JOB 38:12–38:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:19-John3:20\">JHN 3:19–3:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:11-Eph5:13\">EPH 5:11–5:13</a></p>",
